The Commission will hear the testimony of Former Chief Executive Officer of South African Airways, Sizakele Petunia Mzimela. JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Inquiry continues on Wednesday with more revelations on misconduct at South African Airways (SAA) expected. WATCH: State capture inquiry continues South Africa Airways Head of fuel management, Mark Vaughan, concluded his testimony on Tuesday.
He revealed how EML Energy failed to supply fuel to SAA since October last year. Former SAA Chief Executive Officer, Siza Mzimela, will take the stand today. Earlier this month, the commission heard that BNP Capital, a little-known firm which SAA contracted in mid-2016 for a R15-billion loan, was privy to confidential briefings.